oops! in the .login for setting up a "newsgroup of the day"
there is a line "ln `echo $todays_newsrc` .newsrc ". Before
this line there should be a line "mv -f .newsrc .newsrc.old",
or "rm .newsrc", or equivalent. ALternatively in the .my.rn
the line "cp .newsrc ----" should be "mv -f .newsrc ---". 
Either way, it should be arranged that .newsrc doesn't
exist when you start. Sorry. 
